messages.messageBody:
Does anyone remember the Saturday Night Live "commercial" for Swiffer sleepers?!

Julie (-;

Ren Allen <starsuncloud@...> wrote:
"I did actually mop my kitchen floor last week and the warm feeling of
accomplishment will last a month. I'll probably mop it again in
April or so."

The only times I've mopped my floor recently, have been after some
large disasterish sort of thing. First there was a flour and water
explosion (named Jalen) that I thought I'd never get off. Then more
recently, we were firing baking soda/vinegar rockets (film canisters)
across the house and we had that mess to wipe up.

It's hard to ignore white blobs all over the floor, so I mop. The only
other time it gets a regular wiping, is when Jalen or Sierra pull out
the Swiffer wet mop and overspray it (but have a great time in the
process).

Ren
